headline: New House bill revives risk to Intuit’s TurboTax business: BNPP Exane
summary: Investing.com -- A new U.S. House proposal could pose a significant competitive threat to Intuit ’s (NASDAQ:INTU) TurboTax business, according to a research note from BNP Paribas (OTC:BNPQY) Exane. The legislation would terminate the IRS Direct File program but lay the groundwork for a broader free tax filing system that may reach up to 70% of U.S. taxpayers.
